    "extras": [
      "Hungary is in the Schengen zone, so Indian travellers should budget roughly ₹7,500–₹9,500 for visa plus VFS handling and apply at least 3–4 weeks early.",
      "For Budapest, the 72-hour public transport pass at about ₹1,265 is usually better value than buying single tickets at ₹115 each.",
      "Vegetarians should save Govinda Budapest, Govinda Vegetarian Restaurant Eger, Hummus Bar Andrássy and Reggeli before landing because meat-heavy menus are still common outside Budapest.",
      "Cards work almost everywhere, but keep a small HUF cash buffer of roughly ₹1,500–₹2,500 equivalent for markets, smaller cafés and regional taxis.",
      "Parliament tours and thermal-bath slots can sell out on busy weekends, so lock those Budapest tickets before finalising the rail legs."
